        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bias in LLM systems originates at every stage of the pipeline \u2014 from the world's historical inequities, through collection and labelling choices, to training objectives and deployment feedback loops. Each bias type has a distinct detection strategy and mitigation lever. Effective fairness work requires identifying which type of bias is present before applying a fix: a WEAT test catches pre-existing association bias, Fleiss' kappa flags measurement bias, representation gap analysis surfaces under-sampling, disaggregated benchmarks expose aggregation bias, and longitudinal monitoring detects emergent feedback-loop amplification."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Bias is not a single thing to be 'fixed' once. It is a property of the relationship between a model, a dataset, and a deployment context \u2014 and it must be re-evaluated every time any of those three things changes."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
